com.martinambrus.adminAnything.events

Class AAAdjustListenerPrioritiesEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.bukkit.event.Event
      • com.martinambrus.adminAnything.events.AAAdjustListenerPrioritiesEvent

  • public class AAAdjustListenerPrioritiesEvent
extends org.bukkit.event.Event
    Event which is fired up when we need to re-assign listener priorities for some of server's plugins and make them recognize event cancellation for the PlayerCommandPreprocessEvent and ServerCommandEvent events.

    • Constructor Detail

      • AAAdjustListenerPrioritiesEvent

        public AAAdjustListenerPrioritiesEvent(org.bukkit.command.CommandSender sender,
                                       java.util.List<java.lang.String> okMessages,
                                       java.lang.String[] args,
                                       java.lang.String listName,
                                       boolean ignoreLeadingSlash,
                                       java.util.List<java.lang.String> okList,
                                       java.util.List<java.lang.String> koList)
        Constructor, stores internal variables.
        Parameters:
        sender - The command sender that's running a command which in turns requires listener priorities to be adjusted.
        okMessages - List of messages to show to the player when adjusting priorities succeeds.
        args - Any arguments passed to the original command that in turn called this event.
        listName - Name of the list of commands which we'll update upon successful adjustment of priorities. For AdminAnything, this would be for example a list of overridden, muted, redirected... commands.
        ignoreLeadingSlash - Variable to determine whether we should ignore a leading slash (/) in all of the given commands when updating listener priorities.
        okList - A pointer to the list of messages into which we save names of commands and plugins that we've successfully processed.
        koList - A pointer to the list of messages into which we save names of commands and plugins that we've failed to process for any reason.
